      "module_id": 2,
      "topic_id": 4,
      "slug": "dom-inspection-and-manipulation-basics",
      "title": "DOM Inspection and Manipulation Basics",
      "description": "DOM manipulation covers selecting elements to read, write, create, or remove nodes in the document.",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            { "value": "The DOM API provides four primary selection methods: " },
            { "value": "getElementById", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " for unique elements by ID, " },
            { "value": "querySelector", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " for the first CSS match, " },
            { "value": "querySelectorAll", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " for all CSS matches, and " },
            { "value": "getElementsByClassName", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " for a live collection by class. Once selected, content is read or written via " },
            { "value": "textContent", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " for plain text or " },
            { "value": "innerHTML", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " for HTML markup. Classes are managed via " },
            { "value": "classList", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " and attributes via " },
            { "value": "setAttribute", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " and " },
            { "value": "getAttribute", "highlight": true },
            { "value": ". Full API reference at " },
            { "value": "MDN: Document", "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document" },
            { "value": "." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "table",
          "headers": ["Operation", "Method or Property", "Returns", "Notes"],
          "rows": [
            ["Select by ID", "getElementById('id')", "Element or null", "Fastest selection method"],
            ["Select first match", "querySelector('css')", "Element or null", "Accepts any CSS selector"],
            ["Select all matches", "querySelectorAll('css')", "Static NodeList", "Use spread [...] to get array methods"],
            ["Select by class", "getElementsByClassName('cls')", "Live HTMLCollection", "Updates automatically as DOM changes"],
            ["Read plain text", "element.textContent", "String", "Safe for reading user-supplied text"],
            ["Write plain text", "element.textContent = '...'", "String set", "Never executes HTML, safe for user input"],
            ["Read or write HTML", "element.innerHTML", "String", "Only use with trusted content, never user input"],
            ["Add class", "classList.add('name')", "void", "Does not duplicate if already present"],
            ["Remove class", "classList.remove('name')", "void", "Silent if class not present"],
            ["Toggle class", "classList.toggle('name')", "Boolean", "Returns true if class was added"],
            ["Get attribute", "getAttribute('name')", "String or null", "Works for all attributes including data-*"],
            ["Set attribute", "setAttribute('name','val')", "void", "Creates attribute if it does not exist"],
            ["Create element", "createElement('tag')", "Element", "Element is detached until inserted"],
            ["Append child", "parent.appendChild(el)", "Element", "Inserts at end of parent"],
            ["Remove element", "element.remove()", "void", "Modern, removes itself from DOM"]
          ]
        }
      ],
      "examples": [
        {
          "title": "Selection Methods and Safe Content Writing",
          "description": "This puts all four selection methods side by side and demonstrates the critical difference between textContent and innerHTML when writing content. textContent is always safe. innerHTML executes whatever it receives as HTML, which is dangerous with user input.",
          "code_snippet": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <title>DOM Selection and Manipulation</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n  <div id=\"notif-list\">\n    <div id=\"notif-1\" class=\"item\">Deployment completed.</div>\n    <div id=\"notif-2\" class=\"item highlight\">Memory above 80%.</div>\n    <div id=\"notif-3\" class=\"item\">Backup scheduled.</div>\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- textContent vs innerHTML safety demo -->\n  <p>Type anything including HTML tags:</p>\n  <input id=\"user-input\" type=\"text\" value=\"&lt;b&gt;hello&lt;/b&gt;\">\n  <button id=\"btn-text\" type=\"button\">Write via textContent (safe)</button>\n  <button id=\"btn-html\" type=\"button\">Write via innerHTML (dangerous)</button>\n  <div id=\"safe-demo\">Output appears here.</div>\n\n  <hr>\n\n  <button id=\"btn-select\" type=\"button\">Compare all selectors</button>\n  <button id=\"btn-add\" type=\"button\">Add notification</button>\n  <button id=\"btn-remove\" type=\"button\">Remove first</button>\n\n  <p id=\"log\">Click a button...</p>\n\n  <script>\n    var list    = document.getElementById('notif-list');\n    var log     = document.getElementById('log');\n    var counter = 4;\n\n    // ===== SELECTION METHODS =====\n    document.getElementById('btn-select').onclick = function () {\n      // 1. getElementById: fastest, single element by unique id\n      var byId  = document.getElementById('notif-2');\n\n      // 2. querySelector: first CSS match\n      var first = document.querySelector('#notif-list .item');\n\n      // 3. querySelectorAll: all CSS matches, static NodeList\n      var all   = document.querySelectorAll('#notif-list .item');\n\n      // 4. getElementsByClassName: live HTMLCollection\n      var live  = document.getElementsByClassName('highlight');\n\n      log.textContent =\n        'getElementById(notif-2): \"' + byId.textContent + '\"\\n' +\n        'querySelector(.item):    \"' + first.textContent + '\"\\n' +\n        'querySelectorAll count:  '  + all.length + '\\n' +\n        'getElementsByClassName:  '  + live.length + ' (live, updates on DOM change)';\n    };\n\n    // ===== textContent: safe, treats input as plain text =====\n    document.getElementById('btn-text').onclick = function () {\n      var input = document.getElementById('user-input').value;\n      // HTML tags are escaped and shown as visible text — not executed\n      document.getElementById('safe-demo').textContent = input;\n      log.textContent = 'Written via textContent. HTML tags are shown as text, not executed.';\n    };\n\n    // ===== innerHTML: dangerous with user input =====\n    document.getElementById('btn-html').onclick = function () {\n      var input = document.getElementById('user-input').value;\n      // HTML is parsed and executed — <b>hello</b> renders as bold text\n      // A malicious user could inject <script> or onerror handlers here\n      document.getElementById('safe-demo').innerHTML = input;\n      log.textContent = 'Written via innerHTML. Tags were parsed as real HTML. Never do this with user input.';\n    };\n\n    // ===== CREATE AND INSERT =====\n    document.getElementById('btn-add').onclick = function () {\n      var div = document.createElement('div');\n      div.className = 'item';\n      div.id = 'notif-' + counter++;\n      div.textContent = 'New alert added at ' + new Date().toLocaleTimeString();\n      list.appendChild(div);\n      log.textContent = 'Appended: ' + div.id;\n    };\n\n    // ===== REMOVE =====\n    document.getElementById('btn-remove').onclick = function () {\n      var first = list.firstElementChild;\n      if (first) {\n        var id = first.id;\n        first.remove();\n        log.textContent = 'Removed: ' + id;\n      } else {\n        log.textContent = 'List is empty.';\n      }\n    };\n  </script>\n\n</body>\n</html>",
          "output": "The page shows three notification divs, a text input pre-filled with escaped HTML tags, two write buttons, a demo div, and action buttons. 'Compare all selectors' logs results for all four selection methods. 'Write via textContent' shows the input value as plain text — HTML tags appear as visible characters. 'Write via innerHTML' parses the tags as real HTML — bold tags make text bold. 'Add notification' appends a new timestamped div. 'Remove first' deletes the top notification.",
          "images": null,
          "video_url": null
        }
      ],
      "image_banner_url": null,
      "images": null,
      "video_url": null,
      "when_to_use": [],
      "when_to_avoid": [],
      "what_it_solves": [],
      "conceptual_understanding": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            { "value": "DOM selection methods are like different ways to " },
            { "value": "find a person in a building", "bold": true },
            { "value": ". " },
            { "value": "getElementById", "bold": true, "highlight": true },
            { "value": " is knowing the exact room number — direct and fastest. " },
            { "value": "querySelector", "bold": true, "highlight": true },
            { "value": " is describing the person: find the first person wearing a blue badge in the east wing. " },
            { "value": "querySelectorAll", "bold": true, "highlight": true },
            { "value": " finds everyone matching that description. " },
            { "value": "getElementsByClassName", "bold": true, "highlight": true },
            { "value": " is a live employee directory that updates the moment someone joins or leaves." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            { "value": "textContent versus " },
            { "value": "innerHTML", "bold": true, "highlight": true },
            { "value": " is the difference between a " },
            { "value": "typewriter and a printing press", "bold": true },
            { "value": ". textContent types out whatever you give it as plain characters — angle brackets become visible symbols, harmless on screen. innerHTML runs the printing press: it formats and executes everything it receives as real HTML markup, which is powerful for trusted content but dangerous for anything a user typed." }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "common_mistakes": [],
      "bonus_tips": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            { "value": "Spread a NodeList from " },
            { "value": "querySelectorAll", "bold": true, "highlight": true },
            { "value": " into a real array using " },
            { "value": "[...document.querySelectorAll('selector')]", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " to unlock array methods like " },
            { "value": "map", "highlight": true },
            { "value": ", " },
            { "value": "filter", "highlight": true },
            { "value": ", and " },
            { "value": "reduce", "highlight": true },
            { "value": ". NodeList only has " },
            { "value": "forEach", "highlight": true },
            { "value": " natively — converting to an array lets you chain operations in a single expression." }
          ]
        }
      ],
